Bug fix: fixed an issue that could cause JRebel notfications show up in wrong project window. Bug fix: fixed an issue with incorrectly escaped space character in the Run instructions. Bug fix: fixed an issue where generating rebel.xml for many modules caused IntelliJ to freeze. Update: updated the EULA.

JRebel is a productivity tool that allows developers to reload code changes instantly. It skips the rebuild, restart, and redeploy cycle common in Java development. JRebel enables developers to get more done in the same amount of time and stay in the flow while coding. JRebel supports a majority of real-world enterprise java stacks and is easy to install into existing development environments.
